modules.description: This module implements the Louvain algorithm for community detection using a GraphML file as input. It processes weighted, undirected graphs by optimizing modularity through iterative node moves between communities. A concrete use case is analyzing social network structures to identify tightly connected groups of users.

It processes weighted, undirected graphs by optimizing modularity through iterative node moves between communities. A concrete use case is analyzing social network structures to identify tightly connected groups of users.

Implements a function to generate GraphML files representing temporal networks from dated and profile data. It maps temporal interactions into weighted graph structures, where node attributes derive from profile information. This module is used to visualize evolving social or biological networks with time-stamped edges and node metadata.

Implements the Louvain algorithm for community detection using GraphML files as input. It processes weighted, undirected graphs by optimizing modularity through iterative node moves between communities. A concrete use case is analyzing social network structures to identify tightly connected groups of users.

This module provides functions to generate GraphML files from temporal and profile data, and to detect communities in weighted graphs using the Louvain algorithm. It operates on graph structures with time-stamped edges and node metadata, supporting analysis of evolving networks. Concrete use cases include visualizing social interactions over time and identifying clusters in biological or communication networks.
